SIMPLE: pang
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pang
<hw>pang</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. for older
<ets>prange</ets>. Cf. <er>Prong</er>.]</ety> <def>A paroxysm of extreme
pain or anguish; a sudden and transitory agony; a throe; <as>as, the
<ex>pangs</ex> of death</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Agony; anguish; distress. See
<er>Agony</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pang</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pang
<hw>Pang</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To torture; to cause to have great
pain or suffering; to torment.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pangenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
